al dimension to the volume, with highly-experienced academic specialists from various countriesBrings critical theory right up to date with new developments like Cognitive Theory ('Cognitivism')  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh1 aAdams, Bella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllen, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoucher, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanesi, Marcel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuffy, Nikolai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarratt, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGenz, Stéphanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldstein, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarding, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaywood, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLongstaff, Gareth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMac an Ghaill, Mairtin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNally, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParvini, Neema, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlotnitsky, Arkady, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Derek M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharpe, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSim, Stuart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSweeney, Carole, 